com.landenlabs.all_log.alog

Enum ALog

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ALog>
      • com.landenlabs.all_log.alog.ALog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ALog>

    public enum ALog
extends java.lang.Enum<ALog>
    Alternate logging API, which uses a cascaded API to control and delay presentation. By using the ALog API:
    • tag(String tag)
    • self()
    • msg(String msg)
    • msg(String msg, Throwable tr)
    • fmt(String fmt, Object... args)
    • cat(String separator, Object... args)
    • ex(Throwable tr)

    Examples:
    ALog.d.msg("log this message);
    ALog.e.tag("MyFooClass").fmt("First:%s Last:%s", mFirst, mLast);
    ALog.i.out(ALogFileWriter.Default).tag("FooBar").cat(" ", item.name, item.desc, item.tag);

    See Also:
    AppLog

      • cat

        public void cat(java.lang.String separator,
                java.lang.Object... args)
        If valid log level, Concatenate strings with separator

        Example:
        AppLog.LOG.d().cat(" to ", fromTag, toTag);
        AppLog.LOG.d().cat(", ", firstName, middleName, lastName);

        Parameters:
        separator - String place between argument values.
        args - One or more object to stringize.
